{"author":{"id":"c09e313c9fffe8c2e5eaf9906ed0c5e05b746984e42848efce71e23f885e1502"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1526653497,"nonce":"tnT4rc/RwprcAet0XxhZi4xXATI=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzMjQ0MzE5OTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1891","origin":"github"},"title":"meme_chip cannot discover output index.html","message":"Hi,\nI have just recently installed the latest version of meme_chip (see https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repository/view_changelog?id=b50902430e629c0e - Revision:  0:6095db402811) on our galaxy server. \n\nThe tool works fine until the job is finished. I can see that the discovered motifs are printed into folders such as 'meme', 'dreme' etc. These outputs are printed under `database/job_working_directory`. Once the job is finished the outputs in this folder are collected and moved to `database/files` folder. \n\nThe xml wrapper for the meme-chip runs this command: \n    \n    ...\n    #end if\n    \u0026\u0026 rm '$output'\n    \u0026\u0026 ln -s $primary_output '$output'\n\nwhere `$primary_output` points to the parent folder `database/job_working_directory` and `$output` points to `database/files` as the parent folder. So, the last line in the command `$primary_output` assumes the output files are still under `database/job_working_directory`, however, in our case, during the linking step, the outputs are already moved to `database/files` folder. So, the linking doesn't work as expected. \n\nDoes your `job_working_directory` point to `database/files` ? \n\nHave you had a similar problem? \n\nThanks","files":null}]}